### Customer Complaints Analysis Dashboard (Bank of America Dataset)
### Project Overview
This project analyzes customer complaint data using **Excel, SQL, Power BI, and Power Query** to uncover trends, evaluate response performance, and generate actionable business insights.
The goal was to understand complaint patterns, measure response efficiency, identify areas requiring improvement, and build an interactive dashboard that supports data-driven decision-making.

**Disclaimer:** This project was completed for educational and portfolio purposes using a Bank of America customer complaints dataset. It is not an official Bank of America project.

## Objectives
- Analyze customer complaint trends over time.
- Measure complaint response and resolution performance.
- Identify the most common complaint categories.
- Monitor pending and overdue complaints.
- Provide recommendations for improving customer service.

## Tools Used

- Microsoft Excel
- Power Query
- Power BI

##  Project Workflow
1. Data Collection
2. Data Cleaning using Power Query
3. Data Transformation
5. Dashboard Development in Power BI
6. Business Insight Generation

## Dashboard Features
The dashboard includes:
- Total Complaints
- Complaint Trend Analysis
- Complaint Categories
- Timely Response Rate
- Late Response Rate
- Pending Complaints
- Resolution Status
- Interactive Filters and Slicers

##  Key Insights
- Most customer complaints received timely responses.
- A small percentage of complaints experienced delayed responses.
- Some complaints remain pending and require immediate attention.
- Certain complaint categories consistently generated higher complaint volumes.
- Monthly complaint trends revealed periods of increased customer dissatisfaction.

## Recommendations
- Reduce pending complaints through proactive follow-up.
- Improve response turnaround time for delayed complaints.
- Monitor high-volume complaint categories more closely.
- Automate alerts for unresolved complaints.
- Use dashboard insights to improve customer experience.

